title: Jonathan Jiménez
text:
Jonathan David Jiménez Guzmán, known as Jonathan Jiménez (born 12 July 1992) is a <a href="El%20Salvador">Salvadoran</a> <a href="association%20football">football</a> player, who plays as a <a href="midfielder">midfielder</a>.
International.
He made his <a href="El%20Salvador%20national%20football%20team">El Salvador national football team</a> debut on 17 November 2015 in a <a href="2018%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20qualification%20%E2%80%93%20CONCACAF%20Fourth%20Round">World Cup qualifier</a> against Canada, as a 64th-minute substitute for <a href="Dustin%20Corea">Dustin Corea</a>.
He was selected for the country's <a href="2019%20CONCACAF%20Gold%20Cup">2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup</a> squad, after remaining an unused stand-by player for the 2015 edition of the competition.
